    <remarks>
      <attribution license="cc4" from="Microsoft" modified="false" />
      <para>The <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.SizeType" /> enumeration specifies how rows or columns of UI elements, typically controls, should be sized relative to the size of their container. This enumeration is used by the <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.RowStyle" /> and <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.ColumnStyle" /> classes to indicate their preferred sizing attributes. The <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.TableLayoutPanel" /> class, in turn, uses these style classes.</para>
      <para>When laying out a container with rows or columns that have different preferred sizing attributes, any space remaining after the initial allocation will be distributed between the rows or columns whose styles have <see cref="P:System.Windows.Forms.TableLayoutStyle.SizeType" /> property values of <see cref="F:System.Windows.Forms.SizeType.AutoSize" /> or <see cref="F:System.Windows.Forms.SizeType.Percent" />.</para>
    </remarks>
    <summary>
      <attribution license="cc4" from="Microsoft" modified="false" />
      <para>Specifies how rows or columns of user interface (UI) elements should be sized relative to their container.</para>
    </summary>
  </Docs>
